title: Former President's House, aka the Payne house, Moscow Idaho
description: W.L. Payne residence built about 1904 at 514 East First Street between Polk and Van Buren streets on the north side of the street. This was the Paynes' second home and later occupied by several University of Idaho presidents. Payne was an early Moscow banker. Picture by Clifford M. Ott February 10, 1976.
